    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not sure I understand the security concerns.  The generated HTML from the Markdown is run through the IPython HTML sanitizer, which would filter out Javascript and the like.  Routing through the MathJaX engine but not the MarkDown engine is going to be confusing for anybody used to the \"TeXDown\" syntax elsewhere in the notebook.  This is a minor issue for me, so I don't want to press the point, I'm just curious about what I don't understand here.\n"
